<item>
            <title>[WFLY-3430] Recurring Timers are called concurrently</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-3430</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.jboss.org/author/display/WFLY8/EJB+3+Reference+Guide&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://docs.jboss.org/author/display/WFLY8/EJB+3+Reference+Guide&lt;/a&gt; recurring timers should not be executed concurrently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That is not the case. I don&apos;t think the current behavior is actually expected.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
